	<!-- ABOUT SECTION -->
    <section id="about" class="container-fluid content-section text-center">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-12 featuresText">
                <h2 class="text-center">About Us</h2><br/>
					<div class="col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1">
						<img class="img-responsive mugshot" src="./images/Phillippthumbnail.png"/>									
						<h4 style="text-align:center">Phillip Streicher<small><br/>Business Director</small></h4>
						<i class="about-quotes"><i class="fa fa-quote-left" aria-hidden="true"></i>Hey, I’m Philipp! I’m a PhD student at the University of Sussex. I started my PhD with an interest in the way light stimulation can be used to boost brain activity and  positively impact people's lives, but soon branched out into researching both brain stimulation and neurofeedback technologies as a whole. Together with Joseph, I developed a novel real-time feedback technique, that handcrafts stimulation, thereby combining the strengths of the two well-established approaches. Being impressed with experiment results and seeing the potential of the technology as a therapeutic device and cognitive enhancer, we decided that we wanted to make it available to everyone, in the form of a sleek portable device, controllable with your smartphone.<i class="fa fa-quote-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></i>
						<br/>
						<img class="img-responsive mugshot" src="./images/Joethumbnail.png"/>							
						<h4 style="text-align:center">Joe Chan<small><br/>Creative Director</small></h4>
						<i class="about-quotes"><i class="fa fa-quote-left" aria-hidden="true"></i>Hi there, I’m Joseph Chan and deeply enthralled by the Philosophy of mind, Neuroscience, Cognitive Science and Artificial Intelligence which is why I am currently studying a MSc in Evolutionary Adaptive Systems also at the University of Sussex. I love investigating the mysteries of Consciousness, which is what lead me to the Sackler Centre for Consciousness Science, which is where I met Phillipp. In my spare time I enjoy making films and music videos and writing political and psychological thrillers as well as reading hard science fiction. My love of the brain and of the visual arts ultimate naturally found its greatest expression in neurofeedback. When I have a vision of the future, I will work tirelessly to make that vision come to fruition. And my prediction of the future of media is this, that it will be a far more immersive thought powered and multi-modal interactive experience than we can even imagine and I believe Augmind will be the one to make this happen!<i class="fa fa-quote-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></i>
						<br/><br/><br/>
						<p style="text-align:center;">We at Augmind are aware of the wealth of scientific research showing the positive therapeutic benefits of neurofeedback and its ability to boost cognitive capabilities. We want to bring these benefits outside the clinical setting and into the mainstream through an accessible product, giving everybody the chance to excel.</p>
					</div>	
            </div>
        </div>
